This is an official Melius UI-only template.

This template is an owner-focused management dashboard for freelancers, solo founders, and small businesses. Keep the dense practical dashboard feel: sidebar navigation, tabbed workspace, KPI cards, alert lists, cashflow schedules, expense panels, central detail modal, right inspector, bilingual copy, and light/dark mode.

Preserve existing data-melius-ui-id and data-melius-ui-role values unless the user explicitly asks to rename visual editor metadata.
Do not add data-melius-id, data-melius-form, data-melius-action, or data-melius-view in the template source by default.
Do not add src/melius.app-spec.json, src/melius.client.ts, or src/melius.actions.ts to the template source.
If the user asks for saving data, forms connected to storage, runtime lists, auth, payments, notifications, or other platform behavior, add the required Melius App Spec and data-melius-* bindings during the generated app editing flow, not as part of the UI-only template baseline.
Keep UI styling editable by the visual editor: use static Tailwind className strings on real HTML elements inside the template UI kit where practical. Do not use CSS-in-JS, cn/clsx/twMerge, or complex dynamic className construction.
Keep controls visually complete and interactive for the UI preview, but treat them as presentational until Melius bindings are added later.
